From 5be25d21f4e1076795699aa8e8847fcb83b107dd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: fatalcoder524 <11532648+fatalcoder524@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 11:54:53 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] [HACK] module: add module intercept and overlay mechanism

Intercept a module image supplied by userspace and replace it with a copy
compiled into the kernel image, so that a known-good .ko is always the one
that ends up being loaded.

Components:

1. `kernel/module/module_overlay/`:
   - `Makefile`: builds the overlay objects and generates `overlay_files.c`
     from the `.ko` files in `modules/`.
   - `convert_overlay.sh`: zstd-compresses each `.ko`, converts it to a C
     byte array with `xxd`, and emits `overlay_file_list[]` carrying both
     the compressed and the uncompressed length of every entry.
   - `overlay_files.h`: `struct overlay_file` and the intercept API.
   - `module_intercept.c`: `should_intercept_module()` and
     `module_overlay_image()`, which decompresses an embedded image into a
     fresh vmalloc() buffer.

2. `kernel/module/main.c`: hooks the interception into `load_module()` once the
   module name is known, then re-runs the signature check and re-caches the
   section info from the replacement image.

3. `kernel/module/Makefile`: builds the `module_overlay/` subdirectory.

Usage:
- Place a `.ko` in `kernel/module/module_overlay/modules/`, named after the module it
  replaces (the file name minus `.ko`, with `-` folded to `_`, must equal
  the module's own MODULE_NAME).
- Rebuild; matching modules are embedded automatically.
- Success is logged as `module_overlay: %s replaced with embedded version`.

Interception only engages when a matching embedded module is present; the
module loading path is otherwise untouched.
